  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the caption underneath read something like this, that he had a chance with his family to emigrate out of Germany and that he chose to stay with his congregation, that he was deported to the-- I believe they were all deported to the ghetto of Riga and from there deported further, and he and his family perished.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I felt that that was a heroic thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And on the last day of our visit in Rheydt in 1989, I called attention to that fact and I asked those present, both Jewish and otherwise, to-- for a moment of silence for the memory of this very brave man.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- well, Hanukkah and Purim were always times that we put on plays in this little schoolroom.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Somebody built a stage and we rehearsed plays.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it was-- it was as much fun as you could have [LAUGHTER] in a German school, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You didn't-- I had a lot more fun in American schools than I did in European schools.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But as much fun as you can have over there, we had it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As I said, we had-- we had plays and we had celebrations and we had a Sukkot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there were some private people who had a Sukkot and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was particularly lucky, because Hanukkah, of course, we celebrated in my house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then my father had some Christian clients that weren't paying too well, but they gave me lots presents at Christmas time, [LAUGHTER] so I had the best of both worlds.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the people-- our friends in Bonn, the friendship went back, first of all, to my father's college days.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the family name was Steinfeld, S-T-E-I-N-F-E-L-D.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
